    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Areas in a fresco completed at the same level of a scaffolding leaving rectilinear seams in the finished work; generally appear in large Roman, Byzantine, and 13th century frescoes. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
